From the manufacturer

The brighter OLED gaming monitor with a 240Hz and 0.03ms (GtG) response time.

Previous page

  1. The brighter OLED

    With a standard luminosity of 275nits and a peak brightness of 1300nits, this monitor keeps your visuals bright and vibrant, ensuring you never play in the dark.

  2. Micro Lens Array+

    Our UltraGear OLED featured Micro Lens Array+ technology, presents 37.5% higher brightness (SDR) compared to MLA.

  3. The explosion of colours

    DisplayHDR True black 400 brings scenes to life, offering realistic details in both bright and dark settings with a 1.5M contrast ratio. Dive into a more vibrant gaming world with DCI-P3 98.5% (Typ).

Next page

Anti-Glare & Low Reflection

Applying Anti-Glare & Low Reflection technology can provide a better viewing experience anywhere by reducing screen distraction even in the surrounding lighting environment.

Previous page

  1. OLED display with 240Hz and 0.03ms (GtG)

    LGs new UltraGear monitor delivers the ultra-fast speed of 240Hz refresh rate and 0.03ms (GtG) response time on the OLED display.

  2. Incredible speed, OLED 240Hz refresh rate

    A fast speed of 240Hz allows gamers to see the next frame quickly and makes image to appear smoothly. The gamers can response rapidly to opponents and aim at target easily.

  3. Extremely fast 0.03ms response time

    With 0.03ms (GtG) response time, reducing reverse ghosting and helping objects render clearly, let you enjoy the game with smoother movement and surreal visual fluidity.

  4. Technology focused on fluid gaming experience

    With NVIDIA G-SYNC Compatible, AMD FreeSync Premium Pro, and VESA AdaptiveSync, gamers enjoy fluid gameplay in high-resolution, fast-paced games, significantly reducing screen tearing and stuttering.

Next page

Designed to enhance gaming immersion

Previous page

  1. QHD OLED@240Hz from HDMI 2.1

    27GS93QE is capable of up to 240Hz refresh rate from HDMI 2.1. It means gamers can fully enjoy QHD resolution and 240Hz either by DisplayPort or HDMI.

  2. Gamer-centric design

    Enhance your gaming with Hexagon lighting and a 4-side virtually borderless design. The adjustable base supports tilt, height and pivot for comfort.

  3. UltraGear remote control

    With UltraGear remote control, you can conveniently set and control your monitor by turning it on or off, sound adjusting, changing mode, and others.

Next page

Features focused on the gaming

Award winning gaming GUI

Gamers can easily customize settings, from basic monitor adjustments to registering shortcuts, using On-Screen Display and OnScreen Control.

Quick setups for brighter OLED

You can quickly adjust the settings for a brighter OLED experience in gaming environments.

OLED Care

OLED Care helps to prevent after-image and display burn-in caused by prolonged static high-contrast images.

LG Calibration Studio

Optimise colour performance with hardware calibration through LG Calibration Studio for the LG OLED display's wide colour spectrum and consistency.

Previous page

  1. Dynamic Action Sync

    Reduce input delays with Dynamic Action Sync so gamers can catch every single moment in real time.

  2. Black Stabiliser

    Gamers can avoid snipers hiding in the darkest places and quickly escape when the flash explodes.

  3. Crosshair

    Target point is fixed in the centre to enhance shooting accuracy.

  4. FPS Counter

    The FPS Counter allows you to obtain real-time frame rates on how well everything is loading.

Next page

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings, help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Learn more how customers reviews work on Amazon

Customers say

Customers find this OLED monitor excellent for gaming, praising its deep black contrast, rich colors, and easy setup.     5.0 out of 5 stars Superb monitor for gaming, ok for work, nice to use OSD and full burn-in protection
    Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 28 August 2025
    Size Name: 39 inchStyle Name: OLEDPattern Name: 240HzVerified Purchase
    This is an incredible monitor. I tried both 34 inch and 39 inch. Settled on the 39. For gaming 10/10 the additional size over 34 inch is hugely immersive. For work it's a 8/10 because of the lower DPI which does make some text a little harder to read.

    The OSD is easy to use and has great built in features for anti-burn-in and it remembers settings for each port used so I can have brighter HDR for Display Port and switching to HDMI for work laptop automatically changes to my lower brightness reading mode.

    The only negative for me is the aggressive curve. I'd prefer 1800r. Sometimes when moving in a game like an RTS left or right, I can easily notice a weird fish-eye lens effect because of the curve, or trying to view something that's straight and it looks bendy.

    That may just be because I came from a flat monitor so I just need to get used to it. It's definitely a lot more immersive though!

    Overall really superb screen with great colours, all the modern OLED features, and at a really great price.
